<Base title="About · AI Evolution Tree">
  <article class="prose-node max-w-none">
    <h1>About AI Evolution Tree</h1>
    <p>
      <strong>AI Evolution Tree</strong> is a community-curated graph of AI's
      load-bearing breakthroughs — 550+ nodes from the Perceptron (1957) to
      today's frontier models. Each node lists the prior work it builds on, so
      reading top-to-bottom is reading the field's intellectual lineage.
    </p>
    <p>
      The project is <strong>open to collaboration</strong>. Issues, PRs, and
      new node submissions are all welcome.
    </p>

    <h2>Why two views</h2>
    <p>
      Technical writing is too dense for investors and newcomers; explainer
      content is too vague for builders. Each node ships both a <em>Tech View</em>
      and a <em>Public View</em> from the same canonical record — a hedge fund
      analyst and an ML engineer can stand on the same facts.
    </p>

    <h2>How to contribute</h2>
    <p>
      Read <a href="https://github.com/aievolutiontree/aievolutiontree/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md">CONTRIBUTING.md</a>,
      copy <code>src/content/nodes/_template.mdx</code>, fill in the schema,
      open a PR. Every merge is permanent attribution.
    </p>

    <h2>Licensing</h2>
    <p>
      Code: <a href="https://github.com/aievolutiontree/aievolutiontree/blob/main/LICENSE">MIT</a>.
      Content: <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/">CC-BY-SA 4.0</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
